      <h2 class="h2_with_line">
        Here is what you can do with Freewill.js
      </h2>

      <p>
        Here is a standard    <span> Bind </span>
      <pre>
      <code class="language-html">
    &lt;p&gt;
    Here is my friend: {name}
    &lt;/p&gt;
      </code>
    </pre>
      </p>


      <p>
        </br>
        You can use fast <span> Loop.</span> Just use 'i' :) :
      <pre>
      <code class="language-html">
&lt;p s-each=&quot;cats&quot; &gt;
  Meet my Cat: {i.name}
&lt;/p&gt;
      </code>
    </pre>
      </p>

      <p>
        </br>
        Or you can use 'c - from cats' automatically - don't waste your time!
      <pre>
      <code class="language-html">
&lt;p s-each=&quot;cats&quot; &gt;
  Meet my Cat: {c.name}
&lt;/p&gt;
      </code>
    </pre>
      </p>


      <p>
        </br>
        Or you can use 'c - from cats' automatically - don't waste your time!
        <pre>
      <code class="language-html">

      &lt;input type=&quot;text&quot; s-bind=&quot;name&quot; value=&quot;Tomas&quot;&gt;&lt;/input&gt;
      His name is: {name}

      Result:

      &lt;input type=&quot;text&quot; s-bind=&quot;name&quot; value=&quot;Tomas&quot;&gt;&lt;/input&gt;
      His name is: Tomas
        </code>
    </pre>
      </p>

